HEADWORD: dyed
<hw>dyed</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>colored or impregnated
with dye.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>dyed-in-the-wool,
yarn-dyed</stype>; <stype>hennaed</stype>] <ant>undyed</ant>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> tinted.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having a new color imparted by impregnation with
